records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.
On counts 1 and 3, the State moves to delete the enhancers.  Motion granted.
NO CONTEST pleas entered to the amended charges in counts 1 and 3, two counts deliver cocaine.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2, 4 and 5.  Motion granted.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of five (5) years.  That is two (2) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision, on each count, concurrent.
The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of Extended supervision:
1) Pay court costs which include $260.00 buy money and $400.00 warrant fees;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) Provide DNA sample;
6) AODA assessment and follow through;
7) Maintain absolute sobriety;
8) Maintain fulltime employment/work search/ combination;
9) Obtain high school diploma, GED or HSED.
The defendant has credit for 563 days.  (Stipulated by the parties)
Minutes.
